x4freetext: The incident beam energy, 24.55 MeV was known only with
a 50 keV accuracy, and the exact scattering angle only
The overall energy resolution was approximately 15 keV
with on-line division and 25 keV without division, and
depended also on target thickness, and angle of
The scattered protons are analysed by a 180
degr. magnet with a spark chamber in its focal plane.
The isotopically enriched targets were in the form of
self-supporting foils. Target thicknesses were  known
to within +-30% from the target evaporation conditions
Absolute cross section normalization obtained from the
optical-model fits to the elastic scattering cross
The absolute error for the excitation energies is
estimated to be smaller than +-10 keV.
